From the definitions of $a, b$ and $c$, we see that \begin{align*}\frac{ac+b^2}{ab} &= \frac{(-1+i) + (1-i)^2}{1-i} \\ &= \frac{-1+i+2i+1}{1-i} \\ &= \frac{3i}{1-i} \\ &= \frac{3i(1+i)}{(1-i)(1+i)} \\ &= \frac{-3+3i}{2} \\ &= -1.5+1.5i\end{align*}
